It’s tiny, but let’s look inside.  The interesting thing you can see here is at the top, the colour stops halfway through.  Those are our null bytes, they’re all at the top because… BMP files are upside down?  That’s wild!  Thanks BMP people!<% fnrf 10 %>

But, like WAV, you don’t get much from a short README file.  Or do you?

